The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 499)

 His Ziggy Stardust days are long history, but David Bowie?s career has surged on. Around 30 songs are featured in delightful 5.1 surround sound from the 60-odd he performed on the tour. Look out for Under Pressure, where bassist Gail Ann Dorsey does a Freddie Mercury.

 THE DISPLAY 

 (Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm-7 pm, from September 10)

 More than 60 oil paintings by Chandana Hore will be on display at the exhibition presented by the Seagull Foundation for Arts.

 THE FEST 

 (Nandan II, 3 pm and 5.30 pm, till September 10)

 Eighty six short films are being screened daily in two sessions as part of the nine-day festival hosted by Chitrabani and Nandan. To mark the 50th anniversary of Pather Panchali, a seminar-cum-screening will be held on Sunday, 6.30 pm, in the presence of Satyajit Ray?s actors and associates.




